==Notes==
{{note label|Location|A|A}}In some cases, as in this one, the size of the grant was greater than the actual construction cost (as shown in the infobox) because it also included contributions towards the cost of the site, legal fees, etc.<ref name=port/><br>
{{note label|Location|B|B}}The term fanciful in this context means that although the design was loosely based on Gothic features, these were not accurate reproductions of Gothic features.<ref name=pev/><ref>{{Citation | last = Price| first = James| author-link = | publication-date = | date = | year = 1998| title = Sharpe, Paley and Austin: A Lancaster Architectural Practice 1836<U+2013>1942| publication-place = Lancaster| place = | publisher = Centre for North-West Regional Studies| pages = 38<U+2013>39| page = | id = | isbn = 1-86220-054-8| doi = | oclc = }}</ref>

